{
  "texts": [
    "We divided the indomain TED data into two halves, each containing English audio, English transcript, and German translation.",
    "Subsequently, we fine-tuned MT models on each half using the pre-trained models described in Sections 3.1 and 3.3.",
    "Following this, we conducted inference using the gold segmentation with our ASR and MT models trained on one half to the other half.",
    "This procedure generated a synthetic dataset with noisy ASR input, MT predictions, and corresponding gold references, leveraging the provided segmentation in the data.",
    "We then use the synthetic dataset to create instances of document-level post-editing."
  ]
}